  <slide>
    <title>Rehabition Act of 1973</title>
    <contents>
     <div class="quote">
       No otherwise qualified individual with a disability in the United States... shall, solely by reason of her or his disability, be excluded from participation in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to discrimination under any program or activity receiving Federal financial assistance.
     </div>
     <ul>
       <li><a href="http://www2.ed.gov/policy/speced/reg/narrative.html">Rehabition Act of 1973</a></li>
       <li>Civil right (cannot discriminate)</li>
       <li>Organizations receiving federal money (e.g. states, universities..)</li>
       <li>Accessible programs and services</li>
       <li>Preferred accessible format</li>
       <li>At the same time</li>
       <li>Established the <a href="http://www.access-board.gov/">Access Board</a> to develop standards for implementation</li>
     </ul>

    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>American with Disabilities Act (1992)</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Extended coverage to public accomodations (e.g. businesses, non-profits, private education)</li>
        <li>Published standards for:
          <ul>
            <li>Buildings</li>
            <li>Transportation sytems</li>
            <li>Telecommunications</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>No standards for computing and network technologies</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Section 508 Standards for Electronic and Information Technology (2000)</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.access-board.gov/guidelines-and-standards/communications-and-it/about-the-section-508-standards/section-508-standards">Section 508 Standards for Electronic and Information Technology (2000)</a></li>
        <li>Only for Federal agencies and states receiving Tech Act grants</li>
        <li>Based on W3c Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 1.0 Level A requirements</li>
        <li>Estabished US federal accessibility standard for the Internet</li>
        <li>Compliance could be monitored and enforced</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>


  <slide>
    <title>Proposed Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Standards and Guidelines (2005)</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="http://www.access-board.gov/guidelines-and-standards/communications-and-it/about-the-ict-refresh/proposed-rule">Proposed Information and Communication Technology (ICT) Standards and Guidelines (2015)</a></li>
        <li>W3C <a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20">Web Content Accessibility Guideliens 2.0</a> Level A and AA requirements</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

